---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = "2026-06-02";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Creative Journey"
  description="Privacy Policy for Creative Journey. Learn what we collect, how we use it, and how we protect your data."
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50">
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-primary py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center text-white">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-blue-100">
            Last updated: {lastUpdated}
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Privacy Policy Content -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-lg">
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 space-y-8">
            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">The short version</h2>
              <p>
                Creative Journey stores the minimum it needs to run a signed-in account, your
                paper-trade history, and (if you opt in) SMS alerts. We don't sell your data, we
                don't use third-party advertising trackers, and we delete everything tied to your
                account when you ask us to.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">What we collect</h2>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3">
                <li>
                  <strong>OAuth profile data.</strong> When you sign in with GitHub or Google, we
                  receive your name, email address, and profile picture URL from the OAuth provider.
                  We store the email and a stable user ID; the rest is used at render time and not
                  persisted.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Mobile phone number (only if you opt in).</strong> If you enable SMS Buy
                  alerts, we store the phone number you provide and a timestamped record of your
                  consent. See the SMS section below.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Your in-app activity.</strong> Paper trades you record (entry/exit price,
                  share count, notes), tickers on your watchlist, and your notification preferences.
                  These are scoped to your user ID.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Session cookies.</strong> A signed JWT issued by Auth.js so we know who's
                  signed in. No third-party analytics cookies.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Server logs.</strong> Standard HTTP request logs (IP, path, status,
                  timestamp) for operational purposes. Retained 30 days.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">What we don't collect</h2>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3">
                <li>Payment information (no paid tier yet).</li>
                <li>Brokerage credentials or real-money trade data.</li>
                <li>Behavioural tracking, browser fingerprinting, or third-party advertising identifiers.</li>
                <li>Anything from your watchlist or trade ledger that isn't directly required to render the page.</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Why we collect it</h2>
              <p>
                To run the service: authenticate you, render your dashboard, save the trades you
                record, surface the patterns firing on tickers you care about, and — if you opt in —
                text you when a stock turns Buy. That's it.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">SMS / Text Message Alerts</h2>
              <p>
                Creative Journey offers an optional SMS alert program that texts you when a stock
                enters a "Buy" state on your Creative Journey digest.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 mt-4">
                <li>
                  <strong>What we collect.</strong> If you opt in, we collect the mobile phone number
                  you provide and a record of your consent (date and time).
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>How we use it.</strong> Your phone number is used solely to send you the
                  transactional stock alerts you requested. We do not use it for marketing or
                  promotional messaging.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Consent.</strong> You opt in by entering your mobile number and checking the
                  consent box in your account settings. Message frequency varies based on market
                  activity. Message and data rates may apply.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Opt-out and help.</strong> You can stop messages at any time by replying
                  STOP, or by turning off SMS alerts in your account settings. Reply HELP for
                  assistance.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Data retention.</strong> We keep your number and consent record only while
                  SMS alerts are enabled on your account. Removing your number or deleting your
                  account erases it.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-4">
                No mobile information will be shared with third parties or affiliates for marketing or
                promotional purposes. Information sharing to subcontractors in support services, such
                as our SMS provider (Twilio), is permitted solely to carry out the alert service. All
                other use, sharing, or sale of mobile opt-in data and consent is prohibited.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Who we share with</h2>
              <p>
                No third parties for marketing. We use service providers solely to operate the
                product:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 mt-4">
                <li>
                  <strong>Twilio</strong> — to deliver the SMS alerts you opted into. Your number is
                  shared with Twilio only to send those messages.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Polygon.io and SEC EDGAR</strong> — to source market and news data. That's
                  outbound data we fetch, not anything we send about you.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-4">
                We may disclose data if compelled by a legitimate legal request, but we have not
                received any such request and we'll tell you if we do (unless legally gagged).
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">How long we keep it</h2>
              <p>
                For as long as your account is active. When you delete your account, we remove your
                user row and everything cascading from it (watchlist, paper trades, phone/consent
                record, session records) within 30 days. Anonymous backups may persist for an
                additional 30 days for disaster-recovery purposes.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Your rights</h2>
              <p>
                You can view, export, or delete your data at any time from your account page. If
                you're an EU/UK resident, you also have the GDPR rights of access, rectification,
                erasure, restriction, portability, and objection — all of which we honor by default in
                the account-settings interface.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Children</h2>
              <p>
                Creative Journey is not directed at users under 18. If we discover an account belongs
                to a minor, we'll delete it.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Security</h2>
              <p>
                Data sits in a Postgres database with TLS-encrypted connections. Passwords are not
                stored (sign-in is OAuth-only). Session tokens are signed JWTs with short expiry. We
                follow standard web-application security practices but no system is impenetrable; if a
                breach occurs that materially affects you, we'll notify you promptly.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Changes</h2>
              <p>
                If we change this policy, the "Last updated" date changes and material changes get an
                in-app notice on your next sign-in. Continued use after the change constitutes
                acceptance.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Contact</h2>
              <p>
                Privacy questions or requests:
                <a href="mailto:privacy@creativejourney.com" class="text-primary-blue hover:text-primary-purple font-semibold">privacy@creativejourney.com</a>,
                or use the contact link from your account page.
              </p>
            </section>
          </div>

          <!-- Back Link -->
          <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
            <a
              href="/"
              class="text-primary-blue hover:text-primary-purple font-semibold transition-colors"
            >
              ← Back to Home
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
